

1. *(Minute)  *(Hour)  *(Day of the Month)  *(Month)   *(Day of the week)
   (0-59)      (0-23)   (1-31)               (1-12)     (0-6)


2. (*) means that the cron will fire on every change of that value


3. (/) is useful when you want an event to occur every certain amount of time


4. (?) is allowed in the day-of-month and day-of-weeks fields
    It is used to specify "no specific value"